  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here is an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Bank Secrecy Act and USA PATRIOT Act\n- Comprehensive reporting requirements\n- Extensive criminal penalties\n- Strong focus on financial institution compliance\n- Extraterritorial enforcement capabilities\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Centralized regulatory framework\n- Emphasis on customer due diligence\n- Harmonized reporting standards\n- Enhanced cross-border cooperation\n\n3. United Kingdom Approach\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Risk-based regulatory framework\n- Strong international collaboration\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence mechanisms\n- Strict corporate liability provisions\n\n4. Swiss Approach\n- Traditionally more permissive banking regulations\n- Strict banking secrecy laws\n- Gradual alignment with international standards\n- Complex regulatory environment\n- Sophisticated financial monitoring systems\n\n5. China's Approach\n- Centralized regulatory control\n- Strict criminal penalties\n- Limited transparency\n- State-controlled financial oversight\n- Increasing international compliance efforts\n\nEach jurisdiction has unique characteristics reflecting different legal, cultural, and economic contexts.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of these approaches?",
